    "Similarly, SaLoRA [29] also introduces an orthogonality regularization for and; by contrast, it drops unimportant singular values based on the norm.",
    "However, the above methods are not efficient enough for they start with a high rank and then reduce the rank iteratively, which brings a pre-defined budget [30].",
    "To solve this problem, IncreLoRA [30] proposes to start from a single rank and then automatically increase the rank based on a heuristic importance score, where the orthogonality regularization is also involved while the elements in is not required to be non-negative.",
